{"key":"post-17093158","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17093158</id>\n<content>The 6&quot; depth ones are generally superior to clean room filters, which are often 12&quot; thick, but have a lower resistance.&amp;nbsp; You want the higher resistance because it helps create laminar flow.&amp;nbsp; 99.97% @ .3 microns is the flowhood hepa standard.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You study the chart that comes with the filter to determine the right sized blower.&amp;nbsp; Don't try to do it in the opposite direction.&amp;nbsp; Shoot for an airspeed of roughly 100 to 125 linear feet per minute leaving the hood.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can just cover the face with cardboard when moving it or for storage.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17093221</next>\n<prev>17093081</prev>\n<first>17093081</first>\n<last>17093278</last>\n<when>1351116114</when>\n<utime>10/25/12 01:01 AM</utime>\n</post>"}